<%# Phase 7 — Step C. needs_reauth banner.
    Locked decision (7C-banner-color) — red allowed; this is a
    failure-state banner, not a destructive-action UI. Documented in
    docs/design.md (color carve-out).

    Phase 10 polish — consolidated to the single top-of-page reconnect
    surface. The pane-internal `[reconnect]` button and the
    picker-section red banner are gone; this is the only `[reconnect]`
    CTA on the page. Two copy variants based on what we can detect:

      1. needs_reauth + missing the required `youtube.readonly` scope
         → "missing the scopes pito needs"
      2. needs_reauth (default / revoked grant)
         → "Google grant was revoked"

    No internal error-class tokens (`needsreauth`, `transient`) leak
    into the copy. %>

<% required_scope = "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube.readonly" %>
<% missing_scope = !@youtube_connection.has_scope?(required_scope) %>

<div class="flash-error" style="margin: 12px 0; padding: 10px 12px; border: 1px solid #cc0000; color: #cc0000;">
  <% if missing_scope %>
    <strong>your Google authorization is missing the scopes pito needs.</strong>
    <%= form_with url: settings_youtube_connect_path, method: :post,
                  data: { turbo: false }, html: { style: "display: inline; margin-left: 12px;" } do %>
      <button type="submit">[reconnect]</button>
    <% end %>
    <span style="margin-left: 4px;">to grant them.</span>
  <% else %>
    <strong>your Google grant was revoked.</strong>
    pito can no longer fetch YouTube data for this account.
    <%= form_with url: settings_youtube_connect_path, method: :post,
                  data: { turbo: false }, html: { style: "display: inline; margin-left: 12px;" } do %>
      <button type="submit">[reconnect]</button>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>
